==English==
===Pronunciation===
*skrāp, /skreɪp/, /skreIp/
*{{audio|en-us-scrape.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Transitive verb===
'''to scrape''' ('''scrapes''', '''scraping''', '''scraped''')

#To drawing a sharp or angular object along (something) while exerting pressure.<!--not necessarily for any of these reasons: to [[level]], [[smooth]] or clean (a [[surface]])-->
#:''Her fingernails '''scraped''' across the blackboard, making a shrill sound.''
#To remove by scraping.
#:'''''Scrape''' the chewing gum off with a knife.''
<!--not really different from the first def: #To [[scratch]] or [[uncover]] (a surface)-->
#To [[injure]] by scraping.
#:''He fell out of the tree and '''scraped''' his elbow.''

====Synonyms====
*(''draw a sharp objecft along while exerting pressure''): [[grate]], [[scratch]]
*(''remove by scraping''):
*(''injure by scraping''): [[abrade]], [[chafe]], [[graze]]

